        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 6:53PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 653 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 8 miles west of Hobson, or 13 miles southeast of
Stanford, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hobson, Moore, Windham, Moccasin, Ackley Lake State Park, Utica, and
Benchland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
